-- Chad Forces Make Arrests in Quashing Coup Attempt, Reuters Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-05-02T02:45:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/chad-forces-make-arrests-in-quashing-coup-attempt-reuters-says.html
Security forces in the central African
country of  Chad  quashed an attempted coup against President
Idriss Deby’s government,  Reuters  reported.  Authorities who had tracked the coup plotters since last
year foiled the coup yesterday, Reuters said, citing a televised
address by Communications Minister Hassan Sylla Bakary.  Security services made arrests from within the ranks of the
army yesterday, Reuters reported, citing military sources it
didn’t identify. Opposition lawmaker Saleh Maki was also
detained, Reuters said, citing his family.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Nicholas Wadhams in Beijing at 
